  LearningObjectives1Title: 'LGBTQ+ Residents in LTC  '
  LearningObjectives1Text: To recognize the impact of heterosexism and homophobia
    on the health and wellness of LGBTQ+ residents and learn appropriate responses
  LearningObjectives2Title: 
  LearningObjectives2Text: To understand the principle of creating a positive space
    in long-term care
  LearningObjectives3Title: 
  LearningObjectives3Text: 'To learn the importance and use of gender-neutral language '
  BestPractices1Title: 'LGBTQ+ Residents in LTC  '
  BestPractices1Text: Educate ourselves about the harmful impact of heterosexism,
    homophobia and transphobia on the health and well-being of LGBTQ+ residents and
    keep up-to-date with current best practices.
  BestPractices2Title: 
  BestPractices2Text: "Become an ally to residents by knowing the issues, listening
    deeply with empathy and an attitude of openness and respect, rejecting stereotypes
    and judgements, and learning how to be an advocate. (Be familiar with the Ontario
    Human Rights Law and Residents\u2019 Bill of Rights)"
  BestPractices3Title: 
  BestPractices3Text: 'Help create a safe and welcoming, positive space with photo/art/educational
    displays, LGBTQ+ - friendly activities and special events which celebrate diversity
